{
  "stem": "24515.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And any halfway sizable city had a number of them, and they ranged all the way from very practical and scientific, over to what we might call classical, or as I said, humanistic, where they went very strongly on Latin and Greek and humanities and so on.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my father went to one of these gymnasia.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then, he went to university and studied law.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's very interesting.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The way we lived for most of the time was pretty much as people live here, with a very attenuated connection to actual religion.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But when we got a little more interested and a few more things were done, it occurred to me-- and now, looking back on it, I'm fairly certain that he was actually quite well-educated.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Undoubtedly.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Also, that's a little strange.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I know she went to something that we would here consider high school.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't know that she went to anything further, but she was a very well-read woman, and could and did give anybody a good conversation, a good discussion.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I have a younger brother.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, his name in Germany was Horst, but since nobody can say this in English-- they always say horse or hearse-- he adopted Henry, as a name when he became a naturalized American citizen.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So he's now Henry Horst Hartmann.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "About three and a half.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When I was born, we lived reasonably modestly, I think, in a not so very large, but very nice apartment.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I gather, now, looking back on it-- we didn't discuss these things.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We weren't told about this.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I guess my father was beginning to make a name for himself as a lawyer.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And in-- that was-- I was born '22.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
